Before Wilmore and Williams can return to Earth, engineering teams need to conduct more simulations on the ground to better understand the root causes of the technical issues Starliner experienced.

description: A rising trend in Gujarat shows an increase in passport surrenders by individuals aged 30-45 settled in countries like the US, UK, Canada, and Australia. Factors such as better infrastructure and quality of life abroad contribute to this migration wave.
title: Renouncing citizenship: Passport surrenders double in a year in Gujarat

description: Rahul Dravid declined a Rs 2.5crore bonus after Team India's T20 World Cup victory to advocate for equal pay for his support staff. Anand Mahindra praised Dravid's decision, while fans on social media hailed him as a role model for his integrity.
title: Anand Mahindra: ... Now that’s what you call a role model
Nasa telescope captures stunning 'Bejeweled' Einstein ring

description: Project 2025 focuses on a wide range of conservative priorities, including restricting abortion access, rolling back LGBTQ+ rights, abandoning efforts to address climate change and income inequality, and implementing sweeping changes to the federal government workforce. ​​The project calls for the dismissal of thousands of civil servants, expanding presidential power, dismantling the department of education, implementing of tax cuts, banning pornography, and halting sales of the abortion pill, among others. However, the document has faced criticism for its potential to undermine democracy and lead to political violence.
title: Project 2025: Inside Trump's plan to reshape America

description: Former India and Mumbai allrounder Abhishek Nayar could be India's new assistant coach, TOI has learnt.
title: Abhishek Nayar likely to be Team India's assistant coach

description: Former Pakistan cricketer Basit Ali has accused the current management of the team of favoring captain Babar Azam and planning to blame Shaheen Shah Afridi and Mohammad Rizwan for the team's disappointing T20 World Cup campaign. Ali claims the management is compiling a report to blame Afridi and Rizwan for the team's failures.
title: 'Pakistan ki cricket tabaah ho jayegi': Ex player alleges mismanagement

description: The Enforcement Directorate's seventh chargesheet in the excise policy case names Arvind Kejriwal as the main conspirator and accuses AAP of benefiting from proceeds of crime. Allegations include demanding Rs 100 crore for a liquor sale contract and using Rs 45 crore in the Goa elections. The chargesheet presents evidence of financial transactions and communication between key individuals. Kejriwal's lack of cooperation with ED's inquiries is also highlighted. The case raises questions about transparency and accountability in political funding.
title: ED says Kejriwal kingpin of excise ‘scam’, AAP ‘major beneficiary of proceeds of crime’

description: Delhi's power bills increased in February due to a 6-8% rise in the power purchase adjustment charge (PPAC) by various discoms (BRPL, BYPL, Tata Power, NDMC). BJP's leaders criticized the AAP government for unchecked PPAC hikes, while AAP argued it remains constant and blamed BJP-run states for higher costs. Rising coal and fuel prices influenced the hike. The Delhi Electricity Regulatory Commission, under the Electricity Act 2003, mandated PPAC to prevent discom liquidity issues and ensure 24/7 electricity. AAP hasn't audited discoms in a decade. Consumers using up to 200 units remain unaffected from January to April.
title: Delhi: Your electricity bill has gone up, did you notice?

description: Neuralink, led by Elon Musk, is advancing brain-computer interface technology and has moved to its second patient. The first patient, Noland Arbaugh, paralyzed from the shoulders down, successfully controlled a computer cursor with his brain. Neuralink resolved initial issues and aims to implant deeper threads for better signal detection. Musk envisions future enhancements providing superhuman abilities.
title: Elon Musk moving on to second person to test brain tech
US eyes new defensive strategies to tackle China's industrial policies

description: Mihir Shah, 24, and friends consumed 12 whiskey pegs at Vice-Global Tapas Bar (Don Giovanni). Shah's BMW hit Kaveri Nakhwa's bike at 5am Sunday. The bar’s license was suspended due to excise irregularities, selling in non-permitted areas, and underage serving, following the May Porsche accident in Pune.
title: BMW hit-and-run: Mihir Shah, 2 pals had 12 large whisky pegs before crash

description: A senior RSS functionary criticizes Rahul Gandhi's recent statement in Parliament, accusing him of trying to demonize Hindus and spread confusion. The functionary also discusses the alleged political motives behind Gandhi's remarks and the perceived efforts to divide Hindu society.
title: Rahul's remarks a sinister attempt to demonise Hindus: RSS functionary
PM Modi a spiritual person, more leaders should be: Austrian Nobel laureate

description: Pakistan seamer Shaheen Shah Afridi is under scrutiny for allegedly misbehaving with the national team's coaches and management during the 2024 T20 World Cup. Geo News has highlighted Afridi's inappropriate behavior, prompting an investigation into why no action was taken. Former cricketer Wahab Riaz's comments brought the incident to public attention.
title: 'Shaheen Afridi misbehaved with coaches during T20 World Cup'

description: The Texas Super Kings secured a commanding seven-wicket victory over the San Francisco Unicorns in the 2024 Major League Cricket, lifting them to the top of the points table with three points from three games. This marks their first win of the season, moving them from the bottom to the top of the standings.
title: Texas Super Kings secure first win, jump to top of MLC standings

description: England won 2-1 in the Euro 2024 semi-final against the Netherlands, thanks to an injury-time goal by Ollie Watkins. The Netherlands had an early lead, but England responded with a VAR penalty awarded to Harry Kane, who converted it, leveling the score at 1-1. This secured England's place in the final against Spain in Berlin.
title: Euro: England beat Netherlands, set up final showdown with Spain
